╭─ Assistant [MainThread@228244] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Based on the bug report, the `instcombine` pass is crashing because a `poison` constant is │
│ being added to the `InstructionWorklist`. The worklist is designed to hold `Instruction`s  │
│ only, and attempting to process a `Constant` as an instruction leads to an assertion       │
│ failure.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause analysis indicates that a helper function, likely called from various       │
│ `visit` methods within `InstCombinerImpl`, is responsible for this incorrect behavior.     │
│ This helper function simplifies an instruction's operands. When an operand is simplified,  │
│ the original operand is added to the worklist for potential dead code elimination. The bug │
│ is that this logic does not check if the operand is actually an `Instruction` before       │
│ adding it to the worklist.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ My investigation points to the `visitOperand()` function within `InstCombinerImpl`. This   │
│ function is called to simplify operands, and it contains the logic that adds the original  │
│ operand to the worklist.                                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will add a check to ensure that only `Instruction`s are added to the        │
│ worklist.                                                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp                             │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp                             │
│ @@ -342,7 +342,8 @@                                                                        │
│    // If we simplified the operand, the original may be dead.                              │
│    if (Op != OrigOp) {                                                                     │
│      // Let the worklist know that this instruction was modified.                          │
│ -    Worklist.add(OrigOp);                                                                 │
│ +    if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(OrigOp))                                          │
│ +      Worklist.add(I);                                                                    │
│      return true;                                                                          │
│    }                                                                                       │
│    return false;                                                                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
