╭─ Assistant [MainThread@228244] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Based on the detailed analysis, the root cause of the crash is a `Constant` value being    │
│ added to the `InstructionWorklist`. This worklist is exclusively for `Instruction`         │
│ objects, and processing a `Constant` as an instruction leads to an assertion failure when  │
│ trying to access its use-list, which `Constant`s do not have.                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The analysis points out that this happens when an operand of an instruction is simplified  │
│ or replaced. The logic responsible for cleaning up the old operand (which might become     │
│ dead) incorrectly adds it to the worklist without verifying it is an `Instruction`.        │
│                                                                                            │
│ My investigation of the codebase reveals that the functions `replaceOperand` and           │
│ `replaceUse` in `InstCombiner.h` call `Worklist.handleUseCountDecrement(OldOp)`, where     │
│ `OldOp` is the `Value` that was replaced. This `Value` can be a `Constant`.                │
│                                                                                            │
│ The function `handleUseCountDecrement` is defined in                                       │
│ `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Utils/InstructionWorklist.h`. In the buggy version, this     │
│ function does not properly guard against adding non-instructions to the worklist.          │
│ Specifically, if an operand `V` is a `Constant`, `dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)` will fail, but │
│ the logic proceeds to check `V->hasOneUse()`, which is problematic for constants.          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to add a check at the beginning of `handleUseCountDecrement` to immediately     │
│ return if the `Value` is a `Constant`, preventing it from ever being considered for        │
│ addition to the worklist.                                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Utils/InstructionWorklist.h                             │
│ +++ b/llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Utils/InstructionWorklist.h                             │
│ @@ -110,6 +110,10 @@                                                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│    /// Should be called *after* decrementing the use-count on V.                           │
│    void handleUseCountDecrement(Value *V) {                                                │
│ +    // We can't add a constant to the worklist.                                           │
│ +    if (isa<Constant>(V))                                                                 │
│ +      return;                                                                             │
│ +                                                                                          │
│      if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {                                             │
│        add(I);                                                                             │
│        // Many folds have one-use limitations. If there's only one use left,               │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
